This example shows how to build a custom polynomial in order to solve
a rational equation like the one reported here [1]. 

Note that the implementation is partial, since only some multiprecision
function have been implemented and so only the secular algorithm can
be used for the solution. 

[1]: http://mathoverflow.net/questions/120545/compute-roots-of-sum-i-c-i-a-i-b-i-xp


